> +/**
> + * struct ipu3_uapi_bnr_static_config_opt_center_config
> + * @x_reset:	Reset value of X (col start - X center) for r*r calculation
> + * @__reserved0:	reserved
> + * @y_reset:	Reset value of Y (row start - Y center) for r*r calculation
> + * @__reserved2:	reserved

I'm not an expert on camera algorithms, but "r*r" sounds confusing.
What is "r"? "radio"? "red"? or is it something else?=20
Except for "x" and "y" - for cartesian coordinates - whose meaning is
quite obvious, please refrain using acronyms.=20

The main point here (and along the documentation) is: can someone without
NDA-protected documents understand it on a meaningful way? If not,=20
you need to elaborate it.

Also, if you have some non-NDA protected datasheet better explaining
the meaning of those fields, you should add some pointers here to the
section of the docs that better explain them.

> + */
> +struct ipu3_uapi_bnr_static_config_opt_center_config {
